# tkv2 — form model (FieldSpec validators-as-data, reactive errors, validity)

Slice `tkv2-forms` of `specs/ssc-toolkit-v2.md`. Validators are data, so the
same rules run on every backend; errors/validity are computed signals that
stay fresh as drafts change (INT recomputes on read; JS recomputes on change).

[Ctx, component](std/ui/component.ssc)
[field, validateField, form, draft, fieldError, formErrors, formValid](std/ui/form.ssc)

```scalascript
// Pure rules, every branch.
val name  = field("name", label = "Name", required = true, minLength = 2, maxLength = 5)
val email = field("email", label = "Email", pattern = "[^@]+@[^@]+", patternMsg = "must be an email")

println(validateField(name, ""))
println(validateField(name, "a"))
println(validateField(name, "abcdef"))
println(validateField(name, "abc"))
println(validateField(email, "nope"))
println(validateField(email, "a@b.io"))
println(validateField(email, ""))

// Reactive wiring: drafts are component-scoped signals; errors/validity are
// computed and stay fresh after set.
val f = component("signup", "t1")(ctx => form(ctx, [name, email]))

val nameErr = fieldError(f, "name")
val allErrs = formErrors(f)
val valid   = formValid(f)

println(nameErr())
println(valid())

draft(f, "name").set("ok")
println(nameErr())
println(allErrs())
println(valid())

draft(f, "email").set("bad-email")
println(allErrs())
println(valid())

draft(f, "email").set("a@b.io")
println(allErrs())
println(valid())
```
